    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/520.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister to Cuba</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Dominican Government informs the American Minister at Santo Domingo that
                    Horacio Vásquez and the two Rodriguez left Porto Rico today for Cuba, bound for
                    Haiti, where, it is reported, they will receive a shipment of arms to be used
                    against the Dominican Government. You will informally notify the Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs of this, and request full information about the movements of the
                    party if they should come within the jurisdiction of the Cuban Government.
                    Express the earnest hope of this Government that the Cuban Government will not
                    permit any expedition subversive of Dominican peace to leave Cuba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
